{
  "texts": [
    "Moreover, transformers have invasive behaviour because they have the characteristics to be a General Purpose Technology (GPT) in the vast domain of applications in Artificial Intelligence (Coccia, 2020).",
    "The path-breaking technology of transformers is mainly of transformative nature and generates creative destruction (Calvano, 2007), which makes prior products/processes and knowledge obsolete (cf.",
    "Lipsey et al. (1998, p. 43) define a GPT as: \"a technology that initially has much scope for improvement and eventually comes to be widely used, to have many users and to have many Hicksian and technological complementarities.\"",
    "Invasive technologies, as GPTs, exert a pervasive impact across firms, industries, and permeate the overall economy of nations.",
    "Bresnahan and Trajtenberg (1995, pp. 86-87) show that GPTs have a tree-like structure with new technology located at the top of the tree and all derived technologies represented at the bottom of the tree, radiating out towards every sector of the economy."
  ]
}